title: Stade Jean Laville
text:
Stade Jean Laville is a multi-use <a href="stadium">stadium</a> in <a href="Gueugnon">Gueugnon</a>, <a href="France">France</a>. It is currently used mostly for <a href="football%20%28soccer%29">football</a> matches and is the home stadium of <a href="FC%20Gueugnon">FC Gueugnon</a>. The stadium is able to hold 13,872 people. 
It host two <a href="France%20national%20under-20%20rugby%20union%20team">France</a> <a href="Six%20Nations%20Under%2020s%20Championship">Six Nations Under 20s Championship</a> home matches. The first was against <a href="Scotland%20national%20under-20%20rugby%20union%20team">Scotland</a> on February 7, 2015 with France winning 47 - 6. The other was against <a href="Italy%20national%20under-20%20rugby%20union%20team">Italy</a> on February 23, 2018 with France winning 78 - 12.
